==English==

===Etymology===
Borrowed from French. Bon mot: Literally "good word"

===Pronunciation===
bôN mo

===Noun===
'''bon mot'''  (''plural:'' '''[[bons mots]]''')
# Used to refer to a [[clever]] saying, phrase or [[witticism]].  Often used to describe a witty riposte in dialogue.

====Synonyms====
*[[witticism]]
*[[quip]]
*[[remark]]
*[[repartee]]

